-bash-3.2$ dbstart ORACLE_HOME_LISTNER is not SET, unable to auto-start Oracle Net Listener Usage: /u01/app/oracle/product/11.2.0/dbhome_1/bin/dbstart ORACLE_HOME Processing Database instance &quot;orcl&quot;: log file /u01/app/oracle/product/11.2.0/dbhome_1/startup.log  Ignoring the usage message we thought that setting the environment variable was what we needed to do, but&hellip;
-bash-3.2$ export ORACLE_HOME_LISTNER=$ORACLE_HOME -bash-3.2$ dbstart ORACLE_HOME_LISTNER is not SET, unable to auto-start Oracle Net Listener Usage: /u01/app/oracle/product/11.
